# Data Layer Rules

## Types — single source of truth

Types come from `lib/api/types.ts` (generated via `pnpm gen:types` from `spec/sdd-coverage-api.yaml`).
Never write domain types by hand; never copy-paste them into components.

```ts
// ✅ GOOD — within lib/, use relative paths
import type { Requirement, Stats } from './api/types';

// ❌ BAD — same layer with @/ alias
import type { Requirement } from '@/lib/api/types';

// ❌ BAD — hand-rolled duplicate
type Req = { id: string; status: 'covered' | 'missing' };
```

## Errors — Result, never throw

```ts
// ✅ GOOD
async function getStats(): Promise<Result<Stats, ApiError>> {
  try {
    const res = await fetch(url);
    if (!res.ok) return { ok: false, error: { kind: 'http', message: res.statusText } };
    return { ok: true, data: await res.json() };
  } catch (e) {
    return { ok: false, error: { kind: 'network', message: String(e) } };
  }
}

// ❌ BAD
async function getStats(): Promise<Stats> {
  const res = await fetch(url); // throws on network error
  return res.json();
}
```

## DataProvider interface

All providers (`mock.ts`, `live.ts`) must implement the single `DataProvider` interface from `lib/api/provider.ts`.
Selection in `lib/api/index.ts` based on `NEXT_PUBLIC_API_URL`.

## Filter / sort / assess — lib/coverage.ts only

```ts
// ✅ GOOD — within lib/, use relative paths
import { filterRequirements, sortRequirements } from './coverage';

// ❌ BAD — inline duplicate filter
const filtered = reqs.filter(r => r.status === 'covered');
```
